The mirror example is actually a nice physical analogue.

Standing perpendicular to a mirror and letting it bisect your body creates a new object that doesn’t physically exist.

Nothing changed.

Only the boundary conditions and representation changed.

The mirror performs a transformation.

You then reason about the transformed object.

That’s exactly what good analogies do.

